|WKB                          QUEST COMMANDS
|CKB=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

|YKOThe following commands and interactions manage quests:

  |YKBengage waysteward
    |YKOReviews local quests at an area's wayshard or entrance. A bright
    yellow |YKB[?] |YKOmeans new work is available; |YKB[!] |YKOmeans a
    completed quest can be turned in. The dialogue shows suggested levels,
    objectives, prerequisites, and rewards before you accept.

  |YKBmyquests
    |YKOLists all quests you have accepted and their current status.

  |YKBqstatus
    |YKOShows detailed progress for accepted unfinished quests. Use
    |YKBqstatus <number> |YKOwith numbers from |YKBmyquests|YKO.

  |YKBqactive |WKB<number>
    |YKOCompatibility command. All accepted quests track automatically.

  |YKBescort
    |YKOBegins an escort objective when its NPC does not start automatically.

|CKB=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
|WKBSee also: |YKBhelp quests, help quests objectives
